# CupertinoPopupSurface class

An iOS-style component for creating modal overlays like dialogs and action sheets.
By default, [CupertinoPopupSurface](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/cupertino/CupertinoPopupSurface-class.html) generates a rounded rectangle surface that applies two effects to the background content:
1. Background filter: Saturates and then blurs content behind the surface.
2. Overlay color: Covers the filtered background with a transparent
surface color. The color adapts to the [CupertinoTheme](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/cupertino/CupertinoTheme-class.html)'s brightness:
light gray when the ambient CupertinoTheme brightness is
[Brightness.light](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/dart-ui/Brightness.html), and dark gray when [Brightness.dark](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/dart-ui/Brightness.html).
[CupertinoTheme](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/cupertino/CupertinoTheme-class.html)
[Brightness.light](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/dart-ui/Brightness.html)
[Brightness.dark](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/dart-ui/Brightness.html)
The blur strength can be changed by setting [[blurSigma](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/cupertino/CupertinoPopupSurface/blurSigma.html)](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/cupertino/CupertinoPopupSurface/blurSigma.html) to a positive value, or removed by setting the blurSigma to 0.
The saturation effect can be removed for debugging by setting [[debugIsVibrancePainted](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/cupertino/CupertinoPopupSurface/debugIsVibrancePainted.html)](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/cupertino/CupertinoPopupSurface/debugIsVibrancePainted.html) to false. The saturation effect is not supported on web with the skwasm renderer and will not be applied regardless of the value of debugIsVibrancePainted.
The surface color can be disabled by setting [isSurfacePainted](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/cupertino/CupertinoPopupSurface/isSurfacePainted.html) to false, which is useful for more complicated layouts, such as rendering divider gaps in [CupertinoAlertDialog](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/cupertino/cupertino/CupertinoAlertDialog-class.html) or rendering custom surface colors.
